tip.text: Chicken Sheek Gilafi is pretty tasty. Very juicy. The Chicken Makhani was ok. Naans are pretty good. Dal Tandoori was really tasty! And the Paneer Khumb Kadai was pretty good too. Expensive though.
Shanghai chicken fried rice was pretty good. Service is excellent. There was a slight delay with the food, so they served us coke on the house. Brownie points for that 😃
Tried chicken in oyster sauce and Leefu chicken. Both were not bad. The Leefu though looked scary. Super bright green gravy, it was almost like it was glowing.
Barbecued chicken wings were not that great this time. I think that's the biggest problem with this place. Zero consistency. Sometimes it's kickass, sometimes it just sucks.

tip.text: Poori with bhaji + shrikhand is really good here. I didn't like the misal pav much though.
Onion Bhaji with that sweet chutney... Yum!!
Slow service, bad and expensive food. Fried wantons were really dry and tasted a bit stale. Schezwan chicken was some random dish they made up, tasted like some variant of lemon chicken.
The desserts are exquisite! Religieuse and Raspberry Delice(pictured here), try them both!

tip.text: Prawn masala is awesome. The prawn fry was good too. But the Masala needed more flavour. Surmai and Paplet fry had the same issue.
The chicken/mutton thali with wade. The dry chicken/mutton is quite tasty. But the gravy for both were pretty bad.
Ordered a Whiskey Sour. Clearly not what they brought me. But whatever it was, it wasn't bad 😀
Beef Jungle Curry was pretty good! I loved that there was sufficient amount of meat in it. The peanut sauce on the side adds to the taste, but it's not everyone. 😊
The soup filled prawn & pork dumplings were pretty good(don't expect Xiao Long Baos of Din Tai Fung, but it's good). The Fatty Sour drink was really good too, though I must warn you that it's pink 😛
BBQ Pork Belly Bao is frickin awesome!
Pepper crusted beef steak wasn't bad. And the beef lasagna was just ok, the sauce was too sweet. The place is worth a try. Not the best, but I guess they're trying.
